The paper deals with learning complexity and bounds in query learning, which are topics that are typically studied in the machine learning and computational learning theory communities, falling under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). However, the paper also introduces new combinatorial quantities and draws inspiration from model theory, which suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and theoretical computer science (cs.CC). The use of algorithms and computational techniques in learning also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT).
